 Code ki Urdu Explanation:
✅ 1. Public attributes ya methods
Aise variable ya function jo kahin se bhi access kiye ja sakte hain.
Example: account.account_holder
(Kisi bhi jagah se account_holder dekh sakte ho.)
Jaise: account.account_holder

Example: Mona — account ka malik.

______________________

✅ 2. Protected Attribute (_balance)
Ye aik aisa attribute hota hai jo sirf class ke andar ya uski child class mein use karna chahiye.

Lekin phir bhi direct access mumkin hota hai (lekin ye acha tareeqa nahi hota).

Is liye hum getter aur setter methods ka use karte hain:

Getter (get_balance): Balance dekhne ke liye.

Setter (set_balance): Balance update karne ke liye, lekin pehle check hota hai ke value sahi hai ya nahi.

______________________________

✅ 3. Private Attribute (__pin)
Isay class ke bahar se direct access nahi kiya ja sakta.
bahar se access karne ki koshish karoge to error milega.
Python isay name mangling se chhupa deta hai.

Sirf method ke zariye isay access kiya ja sakta hai.

get_pin() method diya gaya hai, lekin wo bhi sirf message return karta hai:
"Access denied. PIN is private."
In ke naam ke start mein __ (double underscore) hota hai.

__________________________________

| Method          | Kaam kya karta hai?                                           |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `get_balance()` | Balance return karta hai (sirf dekhna)                        |
| `set_balance()` | Balance change karta hai (lekin sirf jab value 0 ya zyada ho) |
